  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-08-12",
    "date": "2023-08-30T13:04:19Z",
    "text": "Terrorist Reporting Act of 2022\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Homeland Security to periodically report to Congress information about any non-U.S. nationals (aliens under federal law) who (1) were apprehended by the U.S. Border Patrol after unlawfully crossing the border, and (2) appear in the terrorist screening database maintained by the Terrorist Screening Center."
